section.section:
A written assurance of discontinuance or a settlement agreement may include a stipulation or condition for the violator or alleged violator to:
Pay the costs of investigation by the Division;
Make restitution to the consumer of money, property, or any other thing received from the consumer in connection with a violation or alleged violation of this title;
Pay economic damages;
Post a performance bond or other security; and
Provide information to the Division that is appropriate to assist the public in obtaining relief or to prevent future violations.

When a violator or alleged violator agrees or is ordered to post a performance bond or other security, in determining the amount of security to be posted, the Division shall consider:
The nature of the violation;
The amount of money, property, or any other thing received from the consumer in connection with the violation;
Whether full restitution has been paid to the consumer; and
The risk of future harm to consumers.
